二、指定教科書及參考資料 Textbooks and Reference(請修課同學遵守智慧財產權，不得非法影印)


●指定教科書 Required TextsWilliam J. Stevenson (2013), Operations Management, 11/e, Annotation Edition, McGraw-Hill, New York. (華泰文化)
		●參考書資料暨網路資源 Reference Books and Online ResourcesOperations and Supply Management, 12th edition, Jacobs, Chase, and Aquilano, 2009, McGraw-Hill.D. Simchi-Levi, P. Kaminsky, and E. Simchi-Levi (2008), Designing and Managing the Supply Chain: Concepts, Strategies and Case Studies, McGraw-Hill, New York.S. Chopra and P. Meindl (2004), Supply Chain Management: Strategy, Planning, and Operations, 2nd edition, Pearson Prentice Hall, New Jersey.


三、教學目標 Objectives


Students will develop an understanding of how operations management impacts, supports, and drives a business. The focus will helping students understand the importance of operations regardless of their major or career track. Strategy development, market analysis, value proposition, system improvement and system integration will be discussed.　


四、課程內容 Course Description


●整體敘述 Overall Description- Introduction to Operations Management- Competitiveness, Strategy, Productivity, and Learning Curves- Manufacturing and Service Processes, Process Selection and Facility Layout- Capacity Planning- Demand Management- Aggregate Planning, Material Requirement Planning, and Enterprise Resource Planning- Inventory Management- Scheduling, Production Control, Project Management and Waiting Line Analysis- Supply Chain Management- Location and Transportation Planning- Product and Service Design- Project Management- Lean Manufacturing- Quality Management


●分週敘述 Weekly Schedule





